definition: I would define nature as the world around us that is not enclosed in brick and mortar.  I think that any time I am out and away from cars, building a people and can sit in silence and slowly begin to be aware of the rustle of leaves, the call of birds, the smell of flowers, the buzz of bees, I am in and surrounded by nature.  I can also find the feeling of nature in my own backyard, especially in the early morning before the sounds of cars starting up.  I can sit for a bit under my trees and listen to the silence just for a couple of minutes,  I can breathe in the cool air and smell the mint that is starting to wake up and grow after a brutal winter.  I can hear the slight scratching of my tortoise as he begins to awake after his winter hibernation and the call of my crow family as they come back to my yard year after year,. That is how I define nature.
